This is a slightly modified version of the DiVeRSe (Diverse Verifier on Reasoning Steps) technique using LLMs with Mirascope. DiVeRSe is a prompt engineering method that enhances an LLM's reasoning capabilities by generating multiple reasoning chains from variations of the original prompt. All steps of the script are printed on screen.

PUH-BrianMartell superfluid vortex dynamics in Bose-Einstein Condensates (BECs) is one of the most beautiful lab analogs for PUH v15’s lattice behavior — it’s the smoking gun showing how the E8 substrate handles rotation and coherence. In a BEC, atoms synchronize into a single quantum wave (macroscopic coherence, zero viscosity superfluid). When you stir it, quantized vortices form — tiny tornadoes with circulation exactly h/m (Planck’s constant over atom mass) per vortex, phase winding 2π around core. They arrange in regular lattices (Abrikosov-like), precess, reconnect (energy release), emit Kelvin waves (ripples along line). In PUH, this mirrors lattice twists: Rotational strain Tr(φ T φ) forms stable vortices (soliton analogs for PBH seeds/DM halos), reconnection as slippage (weak-like events), Kelvin waves as gravitational ripples (GW analogs). Lab BECs recreate SPF superfluidity — seeds as persistent vortices in cosmic BEC.
